Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Chedraui, Televisa Decline; Modelo Gains

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-09-19T20:44:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/mexico-stocks-cemex-chedraui-televisa-decline-modelo-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.3 percent to 35,076.96.  Most Mexican stocks followed U.S. equities lower amid
concern that  Greece ’s debt crisis is worsening.  Grupo Comercial Chedraui SA (CHDRAUIB MM), the supermarket
chain based in Xalapa, Mexico, fell 4.2 percent to 33.81 pesos.
 Grupo Televisa SA (TLEVICPO)  , the world’s largest Spanish-
language broadcaster, dropped 3.7 percent to 49.29 pesos.  Consumer staples advanced on demand for stocks that are
less vulnerable to a global economic slowdown.  Fomento Economico Mexicano SAB (FEMSAUBD MM),  Latin
America ’s largest Coca-Cola bottler, gained 1.8 percent to 89.02
pesos. Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC MM), Mexico’s largest beer
maker, rose 3.5 percent to 76.57 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, fell 7.9 percent to 6.10 pesos. Cemex was cut to
“underweight” from “neutral” at HSBC Holdings Plc. It was
also cut to “hold” from “buy” at Banco Santander SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
